#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:0
msgid "Use Remix IDE to work with EIP-4337 and EIP-7702 account abstraction and smart account features on Ethereum."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:0
msgid "account abstraction, eip 4337, eip 7702, smart accounts, remix ide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:8
msgid "Account Abstraction & Smart Accounts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:10
msgid "Remix has functionality for working with EIP 4337 and EIP 7702."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:12
msgid "In the Ethereum blockchain, there are two different types of accounts:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:14
msgid "Externally Owned Accounts (EOA): which require a private key and can initiate transactions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:15
msgid "Smart Contract Accounts (SCA): which represents code deployed on the blockchain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:17
msgid "Until the Pectra upgrade, externally owned accounts (EOAs) could not have code associated with them. Pectra went live on 7 May 2025 and introduced EIP-7702, which lets an EOA attach contract code for a transaction. When an EOA is linked to code (a “Connected EOA”), it can behave like a smart account and gain features such as **transaction batching**, **gas sponsorship**, and **delegated actions**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:19
msgid "For more information, see this [overview of EIP-7702](https://eip7702.io)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:21
msgid "Using EIP 7702 in Remix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:23
msgid "EIP-7702 Template"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:25
msgid "The EIP-7702 template is located in the Template Explorer. To get to the Template Explorer, click the \"hamburger menu\" in the File Explorer, and select \"Create Using Template\"."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:27
msgid "![workspace template section highlighting the simple EIP 7702 template.](images/account-abstraction-7702/a-aa-ws-template-7702.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:27
msgid "workspace template section highlighting the simple EIP 7702 template."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:29
msgid "The Simple EIP-7702 template includes a README file that may be helpful to review as an introduction to this EIP's features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:31
msgid "The Account Abstraction template has many examples and resources for both EIP-4337 and EIP-7702, including a very informative README file."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:33
msgid "Connecting an EOA account to a Smart Contract"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:35
msgid "The 7702 GUI only appears in Remix when deploying to the Prague flavor of the Remix VM."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:37
msgid "![EIP 7702 GUI.](images/account-abstraction-7702/a-aa-7702-vm-prague.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:37
msgid "EIP 7702 GUI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:39
msgid "The **Authorize Delegation** button will open a modal where you’ll input the contract’s address."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:41
msgid "But before clicking that button, first you need the contract’s address — so deploy the compiled contract and copy its address."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:43
msgid "Then click the **Authorize** button and a modal will appear:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:45
msgid "![Authorization modal for connecting EOA to EIP 7702 contract code.](images/account-abstraction-7702/a-aa-7702-modal.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:45
msgid "Authorization modal for connecting EOA to EIP 7702 contract code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:47
msgid "And here, you’ll input the contract’s address. Then, when you hit Authorize, you are creating a pointer from the EOA to the Smart Contract Address."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:49
msgid "Then below the Account at the top of Deploy & Run, you’ll see a badge that contains the contract’s address."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:51
msgid "![Delegation badge containing the connected contract address.](images/account-abstraction-7702/a-aa-connection-badge.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:51
msgid "Delegation badge containing the connected contract address."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:53
msgid "And in the **Deployed contracts** section, you’ll see this:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:55
msgid "![Deployed contracts sections showing two deployed contracts.](images/account-abstraction-7702/a-aa-deployed-7702.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:55
msgid "Deployed contracts sections showing two deployed contracts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:57
msgid "And when you open up the account (which is the new deployment), you can see that it can execute code."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:59
msgid "Account Abstraction with EIP 4337 in Remix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:61
msgid "Gnosis Safe Smart Accounts in Remix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:63
msgid "There is a graphic user interface (GUI) for creating Gnosis Safe Smart Accounts. This allows gasless transactions among other features."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:65
msgid "This functionality is only available when connected to the **Gnosis chain** or **Sepolia test network**. And when connected to Sepolia, a new button will be displayed: **Create Smart Account**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:68
msgid "![Deploy and run section showing a Create Smart Account button.](images/account-abstraction-7702/a-aa-gsa-create1.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:68
msgid "Deploy and run section showing a Create Smart Account button."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:70
msgid "Click on the Create Smart Account button and you’ll get a modal with information about Safe Smart Accounts, which will also show the address of the EOA that will be the Owner of the Smart Contract Account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:72
msgid "After clicking “continue” in the modal, the Smart Contract Account will soon be created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:75
msgid "**Be Patient** It can take about 15 seconds to be created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:79
msgid "When the new account is done “cooking”, a toaster will then pop up at the bottom of Remix with the new Smart Contract Account’s address."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:81
msgid "After the toaster goes away, there won’t appear to be any visible change in Remix."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:83
msgid "Finding the newly created Safe Smart Account"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:85
msgid "Go to the **Accounts** section of **Deploy & Run** and you will see the Smart Accounts. Select the address that begins with \"[SMART]\". The Owner of the account will then appear in a “badge” below it:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:87
msgid "![Deploy and run section showing a selected smart account.](images/account-abstraction-7702/a-aa-gssa-account-select.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:87
msgid "Deploy and run section showing a selected smart account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:89
msgid "Notice that there is no ETH in the account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:91
msgid "Will we need to fund this account before it can be used? No!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:93
msgid "Making a gasless transaction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:95
msgid "Compile a contract. And deploy using the newly created [SMART] account."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:97
msgid "Your wallet will issue you a signature request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:99
msgid "![Metamask signature request.](images/account-abstraction-7702/a-aa-gssa-sig-request.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:99
msgid "Metamask signature request."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:101
msgid "In the image above from a wallet, the Safe address and an address for “Interacting with” can be seen."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:103
msgid "When the transaction goes through, go to Remix’s terminal and click the new transaction."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:105
msgid "![Remix terminal showing the smart contract account and its associated bundler.](images/account-abstraction-7702/a-aa-gsa-log.png)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:105
msgid "Remix terminal showing the smart contract account and its associated bundler."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:107
msgid "You will see both the Smart Contract Account and its associated bundler."
msgstr ""

#: ../../account-abstraction-7702.md:110
msgid "Following [EIP-155](https://eips.ethereum.org/EIPS/eip-155), Safe Smart Account contracts use a deterministic deployment proxy so for a contract deployed using a smart account, the msg.sender will be: 0x4e59b44847b379578588920cA78FbF26c0B4956C."
msgstr ""
